Force a fresh color-theme load on startup so rebuilds apply without incognito

VS Code web persists the resolved theme colors in IndexedDB (ColorThemeData) and
repaints them on startup. The reconcile that re-reads the theme from disk is
driven by the colorThemeRegistry 'added' event, but for builtin themes that event
fires before WorkbenchThemeService attaches its listener, so it is missed. After
a rebuild that changes the Composery theme, returning browsers therefore keep the
stale persisted colors until storage is cleared (incognito / clear site data).
This forces one reloadCurrentColorTheme() after initialize() so the active theme
is re-read from disk (revalidated over HTTP) and applied, overriding the stale
cache. No effect on normal loads where the colors are unchanged.

diff --git a/lib/vscode/src/vs/workbench/services/themes/browser/workbenchThemeService.ts b/lib/vscode/src/vs/workbench/services/themes/browser/workbenchThemeService.ts
@@ -180,7 +180,14 @@
 			this.installConfigurationListener();
 			this.installPreferredSchemeListener();
 			this.installRegistryListeners();
-			this.initialize(previousColorThemeSetting).catch(errors.onUnexpectedError);
+			// Composery: re-read the active colour theme from disk after init so a rebuilt
+			// theme overrides the colours VS Code persisted in browser storage, instead of
+			// the stale colours surviving until a fresh browser profile / incognito. The
+			// registry 'added' event that normally triggers this is missed for builtin
+			// themes (it fires before this listener attaches), so force it once here.
+			this.initialize(previousColorThemeSetting)
+				.then(() => this.reloadCurrentColorTheme())
+				.catch(errors.onUnexpectedError);
 		});
 
 		const codiconStyleSheet = createStyleSheet();
